{
  "text": "In common with the velocity, normalised turbulence intensity is relatively self-similar upstream of the transition (Fig. 11a ) and the vertical distribution is close to the uniform one. Downstream of the transition (Fig. 11b) , the turbulence intensity profile adapts to the downstream roughness: starting with an exponential form characteristic of bed roughness [CITATION_1] , which persists at x ¼ 0:21 m, the turbulence intensity increases and becomes uniformly distributed along the water column.",
